Upgrade WorkflowExecutionService to support parallel node execution.

## Files to Modify
- `src/Homespun.Server/Features/Workflows/Services/WorkflowExecutionService.cs`

## Implementation
1. **Parallel Execution Loop**
   \`\`\`csharp
   while (!completed) {
       var readyNodes = dag.GetReadyNodes(completedNodes);
       foreach (var node in readyNodes) {
           if (!runningNodes.ContainsKey(node.Id)) {
               var task = ExecuteNodeAsync(node);
               runningNodes[node.Id] = task;
           }
       }
       await Task.WhenAny(runningNodes.Values);
       // Process completed tasks
   }
   \`\`\`

2. **Join Synchronization**
   - Track pending join nodes (nodes waiting for multiple inputs)
   - Only mark ready when ALL incoming edges are satisfied
   - Pass aggregated data from all incoming branches

3. **Concurrency Control**
   - Use ConcurrentDictionary for running nodes
   - Thread-safe status updates
   - Proper cancellation propagation

